.TH "drm_atomic_helper_commit_tail_rpm" 9 "drm_atomic_helper_commit_tail_rpm" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_atomic_helper_commit_tail_rpm \- commit atomic update to hardware
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_atomic_helper_commit_tail_rpm
.BI "(struct drm_atomic_state *old_state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "old_state" 12
new modeset state to be committed
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is an alternative implementation for the
\fIdrm_mode_config_helper_funcs.atomic_commit_tail\fP hook, for drivers
that support runtime_pm or need the CRTC to be enabled to perform a
commit. Otherwise, one should use the default implementation
\fBdrm_atomic_helper_commit_tail\fP.
